      serialVersionUID:
      5178569311755396746L

      • Serialized Fields

        • mComponentName

          java.lang.String mComponentName
          The name of the tombstone component object (AssemblyLine or Config Instance)

        • mComponentTypeID

          int mComponentTypeID
          Number, denoting the ID of the current tombstone component. Its values could be one of the following digits: 0 = configuration instance, 1 = assembly line, 2 = event handler

        • mConfiguration

          java.lang.String mConfiguration
          The name of the configuration to which the AssemblyLine belonged.

        • mCreatedOn

          java.util.Date mCreatedOn
          Date object, denoting the creation of the tombstone record.

        • mErrorDescription

          java.lang.String mErrorDescription
          Description of the error, in case of abnormal component termination.

        • mEventTypeID

          int mEventTypeID
          Number, denoting the ID of the event, which triggered the creation of the tombstone. Current version supports only stop events and denote their event type ID with value 0.

        • mExitCode

          int mExitCode
          Status indicator for how the component terminated. 0 means normal termination; 1 means termination with error.

        • mGUID

          java.lang.String mGUID
          Global Unique Identifier is a unique string for each tombstone record created

        • mStartTime

          java.util.Date mStartTime
          Date object, denoting the start time of the object represented by the tombstone (AssemblyLine or Config Instance).

        • mStatistics

          Entry mStatistics
          Entry object, whose Attributes keep various statistics data like number of Entries retrieved, modified, deleted, etc. Only relevant for AssemblyLines.

        • mUserMessage

          java.lang.String mUserMessage
          User specified tombstone message.

    • Class com.ibm.di.api.remote.impl.AssemblyLineImpl extends APIRemoteObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      43495849633090489L

      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject​(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException
          The content of this object must not be serialized. This method throws always. The base class java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject implements java.io.Serializable, so the current class inherits that interface. However the when serializing a UnicastRemoteObject, the RMI framework writes the stub to the serialization stream and not the server object itself. As a result the serialization procedure could never reach the current derived class. and So readObject and writeObject should never get called during serialization/de-serialization.
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException - NotSerializableException
          Since:
          7.0

        • writeObject

                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException
          Since:
          7.0
          See Also:
          AssemblyLineImpl.readObject(ObjectInputStream)
